fi.protonode.reloadingkeystore

Class DelegatingKeyStoreSpi

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.security.KeyStoreSpi
      • fi.protonode.reloadingkeystore.DelegatingKeyStoreSpi
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ReloadingKeyStoreFileSpi, ReloadingPemFileKeyStoreSpi

    public abstract class DelegatingKeyStoreSpi
extends java.security.KeyStoreSpi
    Implementation of KeyStoreSpi that delegates calls to an instance of KeyStore. The delegate keystore can be replaced on demand when the underlying certificate(s) and key(s) change.

      • engineAliases

        public java.util.Enumeration<java.lang.String> engineAliases()
        Return aliases in sorted order. This is different than the order used by underlying KeyStore. Sorting aliases enables user to have expected fallback behavior when KeyManager selects server certificate. This can be useful in cases when client does not set TLS SNI or unknown SNI servername is requested.
        Specified by:
        engineAliases in class java.security.KeyStoreSpi
